Syria is "ready" for the return of refugees, supports the foreign minister
Syria says to be ready for the return of the refugees and is looking for help to rebuild the country that has been devastated since the past seven years of war.
In view of the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem has stated that the country's conditions are improving.
"Today the situation on the territory is more stable and secure thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to recover areas destroyed by terrorists to restore normality.
Now there are all the conditions for the voluntary return of refugees to the country that had to leave because of terrorism and unilateral economic measures that affected their daily lives and their maintenance.
According to the United Nations estimate, more than 5.5 million Syrians have left the country since the war began in 2011.
Another six million who still live in Syria need humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem stated that the Syrian regime would accept voluntary assistance to rebuild the devastated country.
But he stressed that he would not accept any aid under the conditions or by those countries that supported the insurrection.
